name: multiboot2::MemoryAreaType
doc_adt:
Abstraction over defined memory types for the memory map as well as custom
 ones. Types 1 to 5 are defined in the Multiboot2 spec and correspond to the
 entry types of e820 memory maps.

 This is not binary compatible with the Multiboot2 spec. Please use
 [`MemoryAreaTypeId`] instead.

VariantIdx(Some(0))-FieldIdx(None).name: Available
VariantIdx(Some(0))-FieldIdx(None).doc: Available memory free to be used by the OS.

VariantIdx(Some(1))-FieldIdx(None).name: Reserved
VariantIdx(Some(1))-FieldIdx(None).doc: A reserved area that must not be used.

VariantIdx(Some(3))-FieldIdx(None).name: ReservedHibernate
VariantIdx(Some(3))-FieldIdx(None).doc:
Reserved memory which needs to be preserved on hibernation.
 Also called NVS in spec, which stands for "Non-Volatile Sleep/Storage",
 which is part of ACPI specification.

VariantIdx(Some(4))-FieldIdx(None).name: Defective
VariantIdx(Some(4))-FieldIdx(None).doc: Memory which is occupied by defective RAM modules.
